# Lab Name Visual Identity

Color palette, branding, and policies for all Lab Name projects. Inherits format conventions from `styles/formats/`. Color values defined in `palettes/{lab-name}.yaml`.

## First-choice accent colors

When a plot needs one, two, or three colors and no semantic mapping applies, reach for these in order:

| Rank | Color | Hex |
|------|-------|-----|
| Primary | blue | `#0072B2` |
| Secondary | orange | `#E69F00` |
| Tertiary | green | `#009E73` |

## Categorical palette

Describe your palette choice (e.g. "Okabe-Ito, 8 colors, colorblind accessible").

Access: `lab_palette("lab-name")` (R) or `get_lab_palette("lab-name")` (Python).

## Semantic mappings

Inherits universal semantic palettes (see `palettes/_semantic.yaml`). Add lab-specific overrides here if needed.

## Heatmap palettes

- **Diverging** (centered at 0): `RdBu` / `RdBu_r`
- **Sequential** (density/counts): `Blues`

## Dashboard branding

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Title | Report Title |
| Institution | Lab Name -- Your Institution |
| Disclaimer | For research use only. Not for clinical diagnostic purposes. |
| Footer | Lab Name -- Institution |
